									<td><strong>Live Coverage of CNN and ABC News</strong><br>With much demand for the latest news in these troubled times, a new channel has been set up - #newsroom, which uses an eggdrop script to run live updates from the CNN and ABC news rooms. The script updates every 3 minutes so receives the LATEST news on whats going on in the world. <br><div class=newscredits>March 25th 12:02pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:saul_paul@iinet.net.au">Rosko</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="23"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>#Scumshine meet</strong><br>On Friday the 21st March, around 50 people from #Scumshine and ScumShine.com showed their feelings by walking to the state library in protest against the war. Afterwards, all Scumshiners went to Metro Nightclub and enjoyed a night out. We thank all the people for turning up and thank the lovely people who organized the event. <br><div class=newscredits>March 23rd 12:01pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:zaim69@hotmail.com">MyAlbanianAss</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="22"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>Successful Channel Meet</strong><br>The organisers would like to thank all the participants of the #sydney supercruise. Lots of fun was had and we all look forward to the next channel event! The previous meet in Centenial Park saw 60 people attend. Keep an eye out in the <A HREF="http://www.sydneyirc.com/" target=_blank>#sydney forums</A> for upcoming events. <br><div class=newscredits>March 13th 12:00pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:lolly@austnet.org">Lolly</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="21"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>Trivia more popular than ever in #Ibiza</strong><br>#Ibiza has been a very comfortable and relaxed channel over the past few years. Users from all over the world have come and joined us for hours of fun, chat and entertainment. Trivia has been requested by many users and is now in place in the channel.  The bot's name is Elven-Lord or Trivia-Master - to play it there are a few simple commands. To start !start … to make a team !Team team-name ... and to answer a question !Guess answer-here.<br />
Just by using trivia the channel has increased from 40 users a night now up to 70 – 80 users. Trivia has been fun and educational, as well as extremely effective on this channel. #Ibiza also has a Stats bot: Sword-master provides stats to users who type !stats on the channel.<br><div class=newscredits>February 26th 11:59am, Submitted by <a href="mailto:saturn@austnet.org">Saturn</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
